    Description
    Astar
    This is where you implement the A-star search algorithm.
    Bidirectional
    This is the implementation of the Bi-directional Search algorithm for pathfinding.
    BreadthFirst
    This is the implementation of the Breadth-First Search algorithm for pathfinding.
    DepthFirst
    This is the implementation of the Depth-First Search algorithm for pathfinding.
    GreedySearch
    This is where you implement the Greedy Search algorithm.
    GUI
    GUI for the search visualization toolbox.
    Link
    This class represents a link between two nodes in the map.
    Map
    This class holds the map to search for a path in.
    Map1
    Constructs the Main map.
    Map2
    Constructs the Alternative map.
    MapPanel
    GUI panel for drawing the map.
    Node
    This class represents a node in both the map to find a path in, and a node used by the search methods.
    Path
    This class holds a found path from the start to the end node.
    SearchMethod
    Abstract base class for all search algorithms.
    SearchToolbox
    This is the start class for the SearchToolbox application.
    UniformCostSearch
    This is the implementation of the Uniform-cost search algorithm for pathfinding.
